[metadata] {"filePath": "/workspace/answer.json", "oldString": "  "text": "## Servo Shared Style System\n\n### Servo's Style and Selectors Crates\nIn the Servo repository (github.com/sg-evals/servo--be6a2f99), the style and selectors crates are not defined locally but are instead pulled from an external shared repository. According to Servo's root Cargo.toml (lines 160, 178-183):\n\n1. **selectors** crate is sourced from: `git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\"`\n2. **stylo** (the style system) crate is sourced from: `git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\"`\n3. Additional related crates from the same stylo repository include: `servo_arc`, `stylo_atoms`, `stylo_config`, `stylo_dom`, `stylo_malloc_size_of`, and `stylo_traits`\n\nThe Cargo.toml patch section (lines 295-305) shows that if working locally, these crates would be found at:\n- `../stylo/selectors`\n- `../stylo/style`\n- `../stylo/servo_arc`\n- `../stylo/stylo_atoms`\n- etc.\n\nServo's test suite (tests/unit/style/lib.rs) imports the external `selectors` and `stylo` crates as dependencies. The Servo workspace references the selectors crate at line 22 in tests/unit/style/Cargo.toml: `selectors = { workspace = true }`\n\n### Rust Compiler's Proc Macro Bridge (No Servo Dependency)\nThe Rust compiler does NOT depend on Servo's selectors crate. Instead, Rust has its own independent proc_macro infrastructure defined in the standard library and compiler:\n\n1. **Main proc_macro library**: library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs (lines 39-41) - Defines the public mod bridge\n2. **Bridge module**: library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs - Defines the server RPC API using the `with_api!` macro that generates the type-safe Rust APIs for both client and server sides\n3. **Bridge server infrastructure**: library/proc_macro/src/bridge/server.rs - Provides the ExecutionStrategy trait and server-side implementation\n4. **Compiler's proc_macro server**: compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro_server.rs (line 848) - Implements `impl server::Server for Rustc<'_, '_>` which is the compiler-side implementation that handles communication with proc macros\n5. **Proc macro expansion logic**: compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro.rs (lines 17, 33-38) - Uses the bridge to communicate with proc macros\n\nThe Rust compiler's implementation creates a Rustc server instance (compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro_server.rs, line 58) that implements the proc_macro bridge server interface defined in library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs. This allows proc macros to communicate back with the compiler during macro expansion, but this communication layer does not depend on Servo's selectors or style crates."", "newString": "  "text": "## Servo Shared Style System\n\n### Servo's Style and Selectors Crates (External Dependencies)\nIn the Servo repository mirror (github.com/sg-evals/servo--be6a2f99), the style and selectors crates are NOT defined locally in `components/style/` or `components/selectors/`. Instead, they are pulled from an external shared repository managed by the Servo project.\n\nAccording to Servo's root Cargo.toml (lines 160, 178-183):\n\n**Declared dependencies from external Stylo repository:**\n1. **selectors** crate: `git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\"`\n2. **stylo** (the style system) crate: `git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\"`\n3. **servo_arc**: From same Stylo repository\n4. **stylo_atoms**: From same Stylo repository\n5. **stylo_config**: From same Stylo repository\n6. **stylo_dom**: From same Stylo repository\n7. **stylo_malloc_size_of**: From same Stylo repository\n8. **stylo_traits**: From same Stylo repository\n\n**Local paths for development:**\nThe Cargo.toml patch section (lines 295-305) shows that for local development, these would be found at sibling paths:\n- `../stylo/selectors`\n- `../stylo/style` (for the stylo crate)\n- `../stylo/servo_arc`\n- etc.\n\nServo's test suite (tests/unit/style/lib.rs, line 14) imports the external `selectors` crate, and tests/unit/style/Cargo.toml (line 22) references it via workspace: `selectors = { workspace = true }`\n\n### Rust Compiler's Proc Macro Bridge (No Servo Dependency)\nThe Rust compiler does NOT depend on Servo's selectors crate. Rust has its own independent proc_macro infrastructure:\n\n1. **Main proc_macro library**: library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs (lines 39-41) - Defines the public mod bridge\n2. **Bridge API definition**: library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs - Defines the server RPC API using the `with_api!` macro that generates type-safe Rust APIs for both client and server\n3. **Bridge server infrastructure**: library/proc_macro/src/bridge/server.rs - Provides ExecutionStrategy trait and server-side implementation\n4. **Compiler's proc_macro server**: compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro_server.rs (line 848) - Implements `impl server::Server for Rustc<'_, '_>` which is the compiler-side server that handles communication with proc macros\n5. **Proc macro expansion**: compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro.rs (lines 17, 33-38) - Uses the bridge to communicate with proc macros\n\nThe communication flow: compiler (rustc) → proc_macro bridge → proc macros → bridge → rustc. This system is completely independent and does not depend on Servo's selectors or style crates."", "originalFile": "{
